  "prompt": "Could 'The Thing' lift Thor's hammer?",
  "response": "In the Marvel Comics universe, the ability to lift Thor's hammer, Mj\u00f6lnir, depends on the worthiness of the individual attempting to wield it, as defined by enchantment placed on the hammer by Odin. While The Thing, also known as Ben Grimm, is a strong and formidable hero from the Fantastic Four, he is not typically portrayed as worthy in the same way Thor or other characters who have lifted Mj\u00f6lnir might be. \n\nThere have been various instances in the comics where unexpected characters have lifted Mj\u00f6lnir, but these usually occur under special circumstances. The Thing's personality and moral code do not usually align with the qualities needed to wield Mj\u00f6lnir. Therefore, while he is a powerful character, it is unlikely that The Thing would be able to lift Thor's hammer under standard circumstances.",
